Class StartingCabin

java.lang.Object

it.polimi.ingsw.is25am22new.Model.ComponentTiles.StartingCabin
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class StartingCabin extends Cabin
Represents a specialized type of cabin in the game that serves as the starting point. The StartingCabin sets predefined characteristics, including a default number of astronauts and a color attribute that differentiates it from other cabins. It inherits the base functionalities of the Cabin class.

    • StartingCabin

      public StartingCabin(String pngName, Side topSide, Side bottomSide, Side leftSide, Side rightSide, String color)
      Constructs a StartingCabin tile with specified sides and color. A StartingCabin always begins with two astronauts by default.
      Parameters:
      pngName - file name of the tile's image
      topSide - the Side on the top edge of the tile
      bottomSide - the Side on the bottom edge of the tile
      leftSide - the Side on the left edge of the tile
      rightSide - the Side on the right edge of the tile
      color - a string representing the color (or owner) of the cabin
